{
  "root_cause": "Under concurrent multimodal load, the device buffer backing a CUDA IPC handle can be freed/recycled on the sender before the receiver reconstructs the tensor from the handle. With SGLANG_USE_IPC_POOL_HANDLE_CACHE disabled (default False), each reconstruction opens a fresh IPC handle without keeping a cached reference to the underlying storage. This allows the MmItemMemoryPool to recycle chunks prematurely, causing the receiver to open a stale device pointer.",
  "fix": "Set SGLANG_USE_IPC_POOL_HANDLE_CACHE=1 in the launch script. This enables caching of opened IPC pool handles in _pool_storage_cache, keeping references to the underlying device storage alive across reconstructions and preventing premature buffer recycling.",
  "evidence": "Log lines 3614 and 3647: 'Failed to deserialize from CUDA IPC handle (HIP error: invalid device pointer' and 'torch.AcceleratorError: HIP error: invalid device pointer' at reconstruct_on_target_device (cuda_ipc_transport_utils.py:488)"
}
